Errors associated to the absolute activation
Neutron flux has also been monitored by three parallel
plate fission chambers set up at 120 degree in the
plane of the tritium target perpendicular to the
deuteron beam. This flux monitoring system allowed for
centering of the deuteron beam spot on the Ti target
and therefore for determining the actual value of the
flux at the sample and the run-to-run monitor level
Data were taken from table 3 of Revue Roumaine
